<div><div>
<p>Jazz up Confluence with a logo and colours that reflect your company&#39;s branding and name. You can also add a welcome message for announcements or key links that everyone should be aware of.</p>
</div></div><p> </p><hr/></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<h2 id="BrandyourConfluencesite-1.Changethesitelogoandfavicon">1. Change the site logo and favicon</h2><p> The site logo appears in the header and is visible throughout Confluence.  </p><ol><li><p><span>From the header, choose the<strong> cog icon</strong> <span><img src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33581/cog.png?api=v2"></span>, then choose <strong>General Configuration.</strong></span></p></li><li>From the sidebar, choose <strong>Site Logo and Favicon.</strong></li><li>Change the site title and upload a logo. </li><li><p>Select <strong>Show Logo Only </strong>or <strong>Show Logo and Title </strong> depending on whether you wish the Site Title to display in the header, then hit <strong>Save</strong>.</p></li><li><p>To change the favicon, click <strong>Choose File</strong>, add your image, then hit <strong>Upload</strong>. </p></li></ol><p><span><img height="187" width="486" src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33581/custom%20logo%20and%20name.png?api=v2"></span></p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p></p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
